column5: Nice fish but whats up with those gloves you have on?????
No tipping, he was jigging the reefs on Lake Erie with a powder blue Killer Jig with red, white and blue hair -- bare. I know what he was using because that's all he jigs with LOL
From the first 9 days of the season out of Morson on Lake of the Woods.All personal bests. All CPR'd.31", 29", 29".

Not bragging, but I think the picture I posted is still the best photo.....by a mile.....and I can't even take credit for the fish or the picture! Dead fish don't count as far as I'm concerned.........
I've guide 7 days so far and there are lots of big walleye this spring on Lake of the Woods.
What are some of your best walleye photos. Here's a classic from a few days ago........
Caught about 10 more this size but didnt take pic's
Here is Stevensink with a 28" Red Lake Pig and mine too!! MIne might have been 27". Only bad thing was a year ago.
Caught this in 2005. It was released and this is a replica. This is the biggest but we typically catch a lot of fish between 23 and 27".http://i193.photobucket.com/albums/z...06-06_0055.jpg

Ha Ha..... Bob oh, those things are going to eat your head!! **** fine fish!
Those are nice fish, but not mine :-( A friend caught them, back to back, jigging.

No kidding!!?? That's awsome, some big fish in that school! Can you tell what he was tipping that jig with? Thanks. Your buddy is a lucky guy.... ****, even if there not yours, that is still fun to be a part of! Take Care and good luck this season.
